The key WHO actions are:
effective prevention and control of gonococcal infections, using prevention messages and interventions and appropriate treatment regimens;
establish effective drug regulations;
strengthen surveillance systems for antimicrobial resistance, especially in countries with a high burden of gonococcal infections and to expand more countries (>70% by 2030 compared to 36% in 2020) reporting antimicrobial resistance in
